Narrator

Wiktor Smolak, President of Wehlen, had finally agreed to meet with me after several months of silence.

Player_Romus

"The violence you mention is the responsibility of a select few individuals. They are being dealt with."

Player_Romus

"I don't understand. I and my kingdom have been nothing but cooperative in the wake of the Zille incident."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Words, Your Majesty. Only words."

Player_Romus

"Please, just tell me. What can I do to reassure you of your citizens' safety?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I cannot simply hand these people's lives over to a government that is, at best, indifferent to their existence. Who will protect them?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"We've therefore drafted an addendum to the original treaty. A series of measures meant to renew our old friendship."

Player_Romus

"And if this 'friendship' helps Wehlen bypass certain trade sanctions, so much the better."

Player_Romus

"Whatever you believe Rumburg has done or is doing to Wehlen, Rizia has absolutely no part in it."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your continued partnership with Rumburg, in the face of all its efforts to destabilize us, is also a warning sign to me."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Very gladly, Your Majesty."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"As you may know, Wehlen has found itself with an oil surplus due to decreased demand from Rumburg and other monarchies."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"We therefore propose a straightforward exchange of Wehzek oil for Rizian gold. At what I am sure you'll agree is a very favorable rate."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Of course I was pleased that the individuals responsible for the attack were found and brought forward so quickly. Almost too quickly."

Player_Romus

"Wehlen is our direct neighbor and our historical ally. We will always prioritize relations with your country over Rumburg."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Four barrels for every ounce, to be exact."

Player_Romus

"The Queen Mother always spoke highly of Wehzek tobacco."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"If there's one fact everyone knows about Wehlen, it's that we sell oil."

Player_Romus

"That rate isn't favorable at all."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I beg your pardon, Your Majesty, but are you keeping up with current exchange rates? Other countries can only dream of a deal this good."

Player_Romus

"What makes you think that Rizia is in the market for Wehzek oil, President Smolak?"

Player_Romus

"An interesting offer. And the rate is indeed favorable."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"If the price is right, why not? I'm a flexible man."

Laurento Esquibel

"Lespia's statement of support for us at the AN has further increased international pressure."

Player_Romus

"Duchess Azaro, what is the status of our foreign investigation?"

Player_Romus

"Grand Wiseman Ignacius, do you think the religious affairs in Wehlen can have an impact on negotiations?"

Player_Romus

"Duchess Azaro, do you have any follow-up information about the Zille incident?"

Player_Romus

"Ms. Werner, which resources are we able to bargain with?"

Narrator

He looked around the table at Laurento, Lucita, Elena, Sal and Titus.

Narrator

He looked around the table at Laurento, Lucita, Elena and Sal.

Laurento Esquibel

"Even so, we should handle this meeting with delicacy. Any aggression on our part can be used against us."

Laurento Esquibel

"The presence of the Ariana Toras Association in Zille has helped sway public sentiment to our side."

Player_Romus

"To hell with delicacy. Wehlen's never been delicate with us."

Sal Ignacius

"It very well may, Your Majesty."

Sal Ignacius

"Our neighbor has long followed the path of Dastnurity, and I do not fault them for it."

Elena Werner

"A good question, Your Majesty."

Elena Werner

"Gold is always an option. Especially since we raised our stake in RRG."

Elena Werner

"If it's weapons that Wehlen is interested in, we can offer our Dator rifles."

Elena Werner

"We didn't drink it all in Qalus. It only felt like we did."

Elena Werner

"But a country as rich in oil as Wehlen won't need much of it."

Narrator

Lucita smiled warmly.

Lucita Azaro

"And it hasn't helped that pamphlets bearing the group's logo have surfaced in Zille recently."

Titus Gordion

"Thank you, sir."

Hugo Toras

"They have met about it, Your Majesty."

Lucita Azaro

"Nothing conclusive, Your Majesty."

Titus Gordion

"And a set of fingerprints sent by Wehlen intelligence did not match any of the members we have on file."

Titus Gordion

"Not yet, sir."

Lucita Azaro

"Wehlen intelligence sent us a set of fingerprints to run through our database. There were no matches."

Laurento Esquibel

"That's quite troubling, Duchess."

Elena Werner

"They may flat-out ask us to buy their goods instead of trade. But we should be careful with our budget, and anyway, I'd rather not pay Wehlen what amounts to ransom money."

Vina Toras

"That makes sense. They've been missing a piece of their province for long enough already."

Vina Toras

"And why not? We took Iza from them. How much more punishment does their house need to endure?"

Laurento Esquibel

"As a son of Brenas myself, I agree with Her Highness. Zille is home to many ancestral estates of the Sazons, not to mention the Esquibels."

Player_Romus

"I'm as briefed as I'm going to be. Time to go meet President Smolak."

Player_Romus

"What fallout can we expect if we don't come to an agreement?"

Narrator

Laurento looked down.

Player_Romus

"That's true. We're a monarchy. Supporting any kind of people's movement could backfire horribly."

Player_Romus

"Do we even have a majority? I thought opinion was divided."

Laurento Esquibel

"The Zille branch of ATA has already begun coordinating a Rizian-led reunification initiative in the wake of the AN announcement."

Lucita Azaro

"No, Your Majesty..."

Laurento Esquibel

"This isn't the same as the '26 uprising. It's the long-suffering citizens of Zille calling for the protection of their king."

Laurento Esquibel

"If we opted to fund a Zille branch of the Ariana Toras Association, they could coordinate a Rizian-led reunification initiative."

Laurento Esquibel

"It doesn't have to be one or the other. In fact, playing on citizens' sentiments could give us a negotiating edge."

Laurento Esquibel

"He will respect a peaceful transition if one has officially been called for."

Laurento Esquibel

"With enough pressure from both inside and outside Zille, Wehlen will have to give the region back. Or at the very least hold a referendum."

Lucita Azaro

"It's cut off from the Wehzek mainland. Divert enough funding and weapons to the right groups, and we can make an overthrow happen without getting our hands dirty."

Player_Romus

"I see your point, but violence should only be used as a last resort. Otherwise we risk destroying the territory we're trying to gain."

Laurento Esquibel

"The Zille branch of ATA has already begun coordinating a Rizian-led reunification initiative in the wake of the AN announcement."

Laurento Esquibel

"We should not support a referendum if we're not prepared to sway Zille in Rizia's favor. The Duchess and I can agree on that."

Lucita Azaro

"Of course, Your Majesty. But if negotiations fail, things could go south quickly. We should be prepared."

Laurento Esquibel

"I hope you're right."

Vina Toras

"Good luck, Father."

Narrator

Titus and Laurento stood by the door, waiting to escort me to the meeting.

Player_Romus

"Can you two wait outside? I'll be there in a moment."

Laurento Esquibel

"Of course, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"What is it, Duchess?"

Lucita Azaro

"No need to apologize. In fact, I've been thinking."

Narrator

Lucita laughed and shook her head.

Narrator

She held out her hand. In it was a small wooden object.

Lucita Azaro

"Of course, Your Majesty. In fact, I've been thinking."

Narrator

She walked towards me hesitantly.

Lucita Azaro

"Yes, it'll just be a moment."

Narrator

It was a chess piece -- a queen. It appeared to be made of marble with golden details.

Narrator

I picked it up and took a closer look. There was a pair of crossed swords carved into it. The Azaro sigil.

Player_Romus

"Thanks to my father's partnership with Wehlen, those killers were brought to justice."

Narrator

She shook her head.

Player_Romus

"Thank you, Duchess Azaro."

Player_Romus

"I look forward to it."

Narrator

Laurento's face reddened. He didn't speak another word as Titus escorted us through winding corridors to the first-floor diplomatic suite.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"And why not? Our differences aside, there is always pleasure in two world leaders meeting eye to eye."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Circumstances have changed since we last met, of course. But I am confident we can come to an understanding."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Yes, I apologize that it's taken so long. Things are quite turbulent in my country, as you understand."

Player_Romus

"I can't control what the Rizian press says about you, no more than I can control what it says about me."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Really, Your Majesty?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your Majesty, I have the suspicion that your media functions much in the same way as mine. Not a word is permitted that your government doesn't approve of."

Player_Romus

"That wasn't the same. It was a violent uprising led by criminals."

Player_Romus

"You're absolutely right, Mr. President. King Valero should never have asked Wehlen to intervene. "

Player_Romus

"You are right. Neither of us want Arcasian greed to spread across Merkopa."

Player_Romus

"With all due respect, we are. Being a king comes with challenges and pressures that ordinary presidents can never understand."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"And you are hearing this from whom? Be careful what you believe. A lot of false information is circulating about Wehlen at the moment."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Wehlen also has violent uprisings in its past. If they had not succeeded, I wouldn't be here speaking to you today."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But if he had not, you wouldn't be here speaking to me today. Maybe you wouldn't even be here at all."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Are you really going to label me as a tyrant, *Your Majesty*?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"That's how it starts. But give them enough time, and they'll fill the public's heads with malicious lies."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I thought that was the best part of being a king. No need to be accountable to anyone."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Exactly! That's why I'm here today."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But Mr. Alvarez's speech at the AN showed a different reality. You claim to be against Arcasian greed, yet you beg one of its biggest figureheads for help?"

Narrator

Laurento jumped in smoothly.

Narrator

I saw relief in Laurento's eyes.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But what do I know? I don't have to worry about such things, because my people love me."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your family did what it needed to do to stay in power. There's no need to be ashamed of it."

Laurento Esquibel

"King Valero made what he thought was the best decision at the time for his citizens. I'm sure the same applies to you, Mr. President."

Laurento Esquibel

"Lespia's statement was unprompted, Mr. President. It would have been against AN protocol to interrupt it."

Laurento Esquibel

"We're already beginning to find common ground. I'm optimistic for these negotiations."

Laurento Esquibel

"You are correct, Mr. President. As a member of GRACE, our kingdom does not officially support or oppose any superpower."

Narrator

He led us into the next room over, where a set of blue-upholstered armchairs were arranged around a circular table.

Player_Romus

"What about the Rizians whose homes were destroyed by your civil war? You didn't seem to care about their safety."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"As for your own government..."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"You have been nothing but cooperative since the Zille incident, I will grant you that."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your actions in the wake of the Zille incident revealed your true feelings about Wehlen and its people."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Meanwhile, we are worried about the impact the loss of Zille will have on our economy. We will need a way to stabilize our currency."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But do they have access to the largest poppy fields in Merkopa?"

Player_Romus

"Mr. Smolak, we are negotiating for the legal return of my territory, not haggling in some Wehzek bazaar."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"The morphine my country produces has been used on battlefields across the continent. Wars have been won because of it."

Player_Romus

"I've never heard of Wehzek woodcarvings."

Laurento Esquibel

"A few of my family's heirlooms are Wehzek handiwork. They still look good as new after a century."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Indeed, Mr. Esquibel. There is a reason your poorer citizens cross into Zille to buy simple painkillers."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your Majesty, Mr. Esquibel... how much do you know about the Bludish Freedom Front?"

Player_Romus

"They were founded in protest of Tarquin Soll's policies in Sordland. They've been active around the border between your countries."

Player_Romus

"They're a dangerous terror organization whose fight for 'freedom' has cost many innocents their lives."

Laurento Esquibel

"President Smolak, I am aware that the BFF has not gone completely inactive since the retirement of Tarquin Soll. And that they may in fact be gathering their strength."

Narrator

He shook his head.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Forced?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Very good, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"Mr. President, I can't ban people from my country based on their religion."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Derdians are a nationality, not a religion. And Wehzek Bluds are an ethnic group as distinctly marked in their identification documents."

Player_Romus

"Whether Derdian or Bludish, Golcondism is not compatible with Rizian values. That much we can agree on."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"As huge as those of granting a safe haven to radical terrorists?"

Player_Romus

"I agree that closer cultural and economic ties could benefit both of our nations."

Player_Romus

"Tell me more about this trade deal, President Smolak."

Player_Romus

"I'm interested in hearing more about this anti-terrorism pact."

Wehlen Demands

Wehlen Demands

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your family must have discerning taste. But we can also offer raw timber as well as less deluxe furniture at lower price points."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Ah, yes."

Laurento Esquibel

"But you have not yet made it clear what you want from Rizia."

Player_Romus

"I don't see why their beliefs are important. Their motivations are political, not religious."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Their beliefs are shared by the Republic of Derdia. Which has been granting sanctuary even to the most notorious of Bludish criminals."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"This is not strictly about Golcondism. It is about terrorists and those who support them."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"What I understand is that Bludish refugees have a fast track to Derdian citizenship. By allowing Derdian passport holders into Rizia, you may as well be opening your doors to the BFF."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I've been told that your kingdom is about to come into a large amount of natural gas. But your councilors will tell you about the importance of diversifying one's energy sources."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"You cannot get by on your natural gas stores forever. Your councilors will tell you about the importance of diversifying one's energy sources."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Your kingdom may be about to come into a large amount of natural gas. Either way, your councilors will tell you about the importance of diversifying one's energy sources."

Player_Romus

"Your republic is not known for its stability. How can you guarantee that you'll be a reliable trading partner?"

Player_Romus

"You may be right. Access to oil alongside natural gas would grant us more flexibility, not to mention more options for trade with our neighbors."

Player_Romus

"Rizia already has all the energy it needs, Mr. President. We do not wish to purchase more."

Player_Romus

"Yes, there's no guarantee we'll be awarded any part of that gas field. Having a backup energy source might be prudent."

Laurento Esquibel

"Correct, Your Majesty. Until the final agreement is signed, we cannot rely on access to the Aureus field for our energy needs or any other country's."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"As long as I am president of Wehlen, the oil will keep flowing. That much, I can promise you."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But of course, there are ways that Rizia can help Wehlen remain stable. As we have already discussed."

Laurento Esquibel

"Both of you are correct. Oil has uses that natural gas does not -- and vice versa."

Laurento Esquibel

"I will remind you all that Wehlen is under partial sanctions by most of the West."

Laurento Esquibel

"The one commodity they have been trading freely is oil, but the embargo we agreed on with Rumburg has been slowing that down."

Player_Romus

"Is the bilateral migration agreement what it sounds like?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"And they are not acting alone. Their so-called fight for 'peace' is in reality a mass destabilization effort funded by the West."

Player_Romus

"I hope you have concrete evidence to back up that accusation, Mr. President."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Then perhaps you should ask Her Excellency to fill you in the next time you sit down for tea."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"There is no honor among criminals, Your Majesty."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Believe it or don't believe it, Your Majesty. The effects of their bloody crusade will be the same."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Unless..."

Player_Romus

"Unless what?"

Player_Romus

"No need to go on. We'll find a compromise that allows us to keep Derdia out of the ban."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Well, Your Majesty, let's say the Republic of Wehlen decided to take a more proactive approach to the BFF problem."

Laurento Esquibel

"Indeed not, President Smolak. I hope that your so-called solution does not involve retaliatory violence."

Laurento Esquibel

"It sounds as if the President of Wehlen is asking for the intervention of the Rizian military."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Or..."

Player_Romus

"Or what?"

Player_Romus

"I don't need to hear another option. We'll include Derdia in the agreement if we need to."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Nothing so vulgar, Mr. Esquibel."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Yes! See, Wehlen and Rizia have much in common."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"And in that case, we would be most grateful if the Rizian Navy prevented them from reaching their destination."

Player_Romus

"Our navy is currently preoccupied with Pales."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I am not asking for your help today. Only someday."

Player_Romus

"This is your battle to fight, President Smolak. Not Rizia's."

Player_Romus

"I see. A small contribution towards the greater fight against terrorism."

Player_Romus

"You are asking too much of my country, President Smolak."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But I am also happy to discuss our other terms."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"All of us must do our part in the fight against Bludish extremism and Western influence, Your Majesty."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Wehlen and Rizia arm in arm, neutralizing the double threat of Bludish extremism and Western influence. Just imagine."

Player_Romus

"That's too good of a rate to be true. There must be a catch."

Laurento Esquibel

"Even if the AN rules in our favor, we can still use oil for trade with our other neighbors."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"But I have concerns about the consistency of your supply."

Player_Romus

"Nonsense, Mr. President. Our mining output is as robust as it's ever been."

Player_Romus

"As a stakeholder in Rizia's royal mining company, I have a vested interest in keeping gold production consistent."

Player_Romus

"Our new regulations may have slowed production temporarily, but I assure you they will be good for productivity in the long run."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"So you say. Time will tell."

Player_Romus

"Are you referring to Morella's talk at the AN? I hope you don't actually believe in Prime Minister Saltana's empty threats."

Laurento Esquibel

"However, we have other commodities that we can offer instead of or in addition to gold. Would those be of interest?"

Laurento Esquibel

"We are as interested in a fair deal as you are.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I believe so."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Yes, I appreciated your decree. I am sure the Rizian economy did as well."

Player_Romus

"Such an agreement would open the floodgates for an uncontrollable migration wave."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"There would be no 'floodgates', Your Majesty. My government is prepared to assist in the transition."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I don't understand. The king makes the decisions, no?"

Laurento Esquibel

"Mr. Smolak, Mr. President, I agree that the Wehzeks who have made Zille their home should be allowed to continue living and working there. That was part of the original treaty as well."

Player_Romus

"I can extend those rights to the Wehzeks currently living in Zille. But to every citizen in Wehlen?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Even more so, I suspect. But we need to make sure all options have been laid on the table."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"And has the economy suffered for it? Quite the opposite, I'll wager."

Laurento Esquibel

"If it were highly regulated, the integration of Wehzeks into the Rizian work force could be more of a benefit than a drawback."

Player_Romus

"I must abide by the advice of my councilors and the House of Delegates. None of whom want citizens of your country flooding mine."

Player_Romus

"To make such a powerful decree would be an abuse of my authority. I cannot do it without first consulting with my most trusted officials."

Laurento Esquibel

"With that said, Mr. Smolak, are you not worried about a potential loss of skilled workers as Wehzeks seek higher compensation in Rizia?"

Laurento Esquibel

"But to extend those rights to anyone coming from Wehlen... it would have to be done smoothly and carefully to avoid overloading our social services."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Of course I have thought about that. But the trade agreement I have already proposed will help level out the economic disparities between our nations."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"You asked for Wehlen's help in the past. We are only asking that the favor be returned."

Laurento Esquibel

"But I agree that promising any more could prove dangerous. Rizia's social services are budgeted and scaled to serve our citizens alone. We can't risk overloading them."

Player_Romus

"Good point. I have nothing but compassion for the citizens of Wehlen, but Rizia will always come first."

Player_Romus

"That is debatable, Mr. Esquibel. The economic benefits of better integrating our two countries might offset the cost."

Laurento Esquibel

"And indeed, the new handover plan his ministers are now proposing has a three-year timeline attached to it."

Player_Romus

"Three years is nothing in the grand scheme of my lengthy reign. I am willing to wait."

Laurento Esquibel

"My deepest apologies, Your Majesty. As I said, this is an unprecedented situation, and I have been trying my best to find a way out of it."

Laurento Esquibel

"As I said, this is an unprecedented situation. I believe the AN is satisfied that President Smolak has set a new deadline at all."

Laurento Esquibel

"I am glad you see it that way, Your Majesty. The more desperate we seem, the more Wehlen will feel entitled to demand from us."

Lucita Azaro

"And what makes us think that this one will be met when the last one was not?"

Lucita Azaro

"This is our territory. Why are we not setting the agenda?"

Vina Toras

"I'm surprised the international community is not challenging an oppressive man like President Smolak."

Narrator

Laurento opened his notebook.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Yet you remain closely tied to Rumburg, a nation that is clearly oriented towards Arcasia and the West despite all pretenses to the contrary."

Narrator

President Smolak smiled just a little too widely.

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Rizia above all. I feel like I have heard that somewhere before."

Player_Romus

"So you are trying to drag Rizia down to Wehlen's level."

Player_Romus

"It will take more than a trade deal to repair Wehlen's damage, Mr. Smolak."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"We are a diamond in the rough, Your Majesty. Set us in gold, and we will shine."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I like your way of thinking."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"No, Your Majesty. It is not 'enough' that your country has grown to rely on the cheap labor of a Wehzek underclass."

Narrator

Laurento took one last glance at his folder, then looked up at us both.

Laurento Esquibel

"I believe we've covered everything, gentlemen."

Player_Romus

"Not everything. What about this three-year timeline?"

Player_Romus

"Everything except for which of these measures will actually be implemented and how."

Player_Romus

"I still believe President Smolak is asking for too much. Especially in light of Wehlen's poor international standing."

Laurento Esquibel

"Yes, well, that's still to be decided upon."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"The timeline is to ensure that your kingdom can be relied upon, Your Majesty."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"So we are asking for a three-year probationary period. If all is still well between Wehlen and Rizia by the end of that time, we will be able to return Zille with full confidence."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Perhaps you're new to negotiation, Your Majesty? We start high and end up somewhere in the middle."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"You are in no position to be saying that to me, Your Majesty. But I will remain in this room out of courtesy for you and your kingdom."

Player_Romus

"Do not doubt my kingdom's ability to deliver on its promises."

Player_Romus

"When will it end? How can I be sure that three years won't turn into ten?"

Laurento Esquibel

"Would you mind waiting in the sitting room while His Majesty and I decide on Rizia's half of the agreement?"

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"It would be my pleasure."

Narrator

Smolak exited the room backwards, bowing as he did so.

Laurento Esquibel

"Well. Quite a lot to think about, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"I'm ready to get this over with."

Player_Romus

"I have a few more questions, if you please."

Player_Romus

"I still feel Mr. Smolak is demanding too much."

Player_Romus

"What will the impact be if I enact the bans he's asking for?"

Player_Romus

"I'm confused about this trade deal he's asking for. Do we need to import and export exactly the same amount of goods?"

Player_Romus

"Granting Wehzeks full rights in Rizia... do you think that's a good idea?"

Laurento Esquibel

"That depends, Your Majesty."

Narrator

My foreign councilor looked troubled.

Player_Romus

"I understand."

Laurento Esquibel

"Not necessarily, Your Majesty."

Laurento Esquibel

"The ban on Bluds should not ruffle as many feathers. Though if the rumors concerning Rumburg's support of the BFF are true, we do risk raising the ire of Her Excellency."

Player_Romus

"I appreciate your efforts to keep the peace. But even you must realize that a diplomatic handover was never in the cards. Not as long as that guy's in charge of Wehlen."

Laurento Esquibel

"I know President Smolak is an eccentric man. But I do believe his primary intention is to end Wehlen's isolation."

Laurento Esquibel

"I suppose so. I must warn you, those could end up costing us far more dearly than a few trade and border concessions."

Laurento Esquibel

"If he feels he has an ally in Rizia, there will be no reason for him to keep control of Zille."

Wehlen Demands Last Qs

Wehlen Demands Last Qs

Laurento Esquibel

"As a matter of fact, we're in a position to make a very advantageous deal. Especially if we meet the President's other demands."

Laurento Esquibel

"In fact, if we don't want to make too many concessions in other areas, we may have to settle for a lopsided deal."

Laurento Esquibel
